The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Tuesday, June 14, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Siliguri, June 13: Several Siliguri Institute of Technology teachers have been assaulted following tension over students demand that they be allowed to cheat during the semester exam.

 When a third year BTech student was not allowed to copy during Saturdays exam, her classmates demanded that they all be allowed to refer to textbooks as their teachers had failed to cover the syllabus. The authorities were forced to call police today and the exam began after a half-an-hour break. Principal A.R. Nath said a probe has been ordered. 

 Calcutta: The high court on Monday directed the government to allow the mother of a newborn to sit for the Basic Training final examination from June 17. A college in Purulia had restrained Nivedita Das from taking the exam because of pregnancy.

 Santiniketan: Visva-Bharati has extended its summer vacation for an indefinite period because of the agitation by non-teaching staff since May 6. They have been protesting against recruitment of private guards.




